# 🦷 AI Dental Voice Bot: System Workflow

This document outlines the current state of the backend architecture and exactly how the data will flow once Vapi is fully integrated.

## 🏗️ What We Have Built So Far

Right now, we have completed the **Core Backend Engine**. Think of this as the brain and memory of the system that sits quietly waiting for Vapi to talk to it.

1. **Database Layer (Supabase)**
   * **[clinics](file:///c:/Users/vivek/Documents/Voice%20Bot/backend/app/api/routes/clinics.py#5-8) table**: Stores the dental practices.
   * **[leads](file:///c:/Users/vivek/Documents/Voice%20Bot/backend/app/api/routes/leads.py#8-19) table**: Stores the actual appointments/calls.
2. **Server Layer (FastAPI)**
   * **`GET /leads`**: For fetching existing leads (will be used by your future frontend dashboard).
   * **`PATCH /leads/{id}/status`**: To update a lead from "pending" to "booked" or "contacted".
   * **`POST /webhook/vapi`**: The golden endpoint. This is the "receiver" that Vapi will send data to.
3. **Async Processing (`BackgroundTasks`)**
   * An SMS system that fires silently in the background so it doesn't slow down the AI conversation.

---

## 📞 How the Workflow WILL Go (Once Vapi is Plugged In)

Here is the exact step-by-step journey of a phone call:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Patient
    participant Vapi as Vapi (AI Voice Agent)
    participant FastAPI as Our Backend (/webhook/vapi)
    participant Database as Supabase DB
    participant SMS as Async SMS Service

    %% The Call
    Patient->>Vapi: *Calls the phone number*
    Vapi->>Patient: "Hello! This is Main Street Dental. How can I help?"
    Patient->>Vapi: "I need to book a cleaning on Monday morning."
    
    %% The AI Processing
    Note over Vapi: Vapi collects name, phone, date, and intent.
    Vapi->>Patient: "Great, I have you down for Monday morning. We will text you a confirmation."
    
    %% The Webhook Trigger (This is where our code kicks in)
    Note over Vapi: Call Ends. Vapi formats the collected data into JSON.
    Vapi->>FastAPI: POST /webhook/vapi (Sends the JSON payload)
    
    %% Backend Magic
    Note over FastAPI: FastAPI validates the payload structure.
    FastAPI->>Database: INSERT INTO leads (Patient Data)
    Database-->>FastAPI: Returns new Lead ID
    
    %% Async task handoff
    FastAPI-)SMS: Trigger background SMS job
    
    %% Immediate Response
    FastAPI-->>Vapi: HTTP 200 OK {"status": "success"} (Extremely fast)
    
    %% Background task execution
    Note over SMS: Wait 2 seconds (simulate SMS delivery time)
    SMS->>Patient: *Text Message*: "Hi, your appt is confirmed!"
```

### 1️⃣ The Conversation (Inside Vapi)
A patient dials the Twilio/Vapi phone number. The Vapi Assistant picks up and follows the tight System Prompt we discussed (short, professional answers, collecting structured data).

### 2️⃣ The Webhook Fire (Vapi -> FastAPI)
Once Vapi finishes the call (or during the call if you configure a specific booking function/tool), Vapi packages the information the AI gathered into a neat JSON box and sends an HTTP POST request to our `/webhook/vapi` endpoint.

### 3️⃣ The Backend Catch (FastAPI)
Our backend receives the JSON. Because we defined strict Pydantic models ([LeadCreate](file:///c:/Users/vivek/Documents/Voice%20Bot/backend/app/models/lead.py#4-14)), FastAPI instantly checks: *"Does this data have a clinic_id? Does it look right?"*

### 4️⃣ The Database Save & Fast Reply (FastAPI -> Supabase)
FastAPI bypasses Row Level Security using our **Service Role Key** and instantly saves the Lead into the Supabase [leads](file:///c:/Users/vivek/Documents/Voice%20Bot/backend/app/api/routes/leads.py#8-19) table. 
FastAPI then immediately shoots a `200 OK {"status": "success"}` back to Vapi so Vapi knows the job is done and doesn't crash or retry.

### 5️⃣ The Background Task (FastAPI -> SMS)
Behind the scenes, completely detached from the Vapi request, FastAPI passes the phone number to our [send_sms](file:///c:/Users/vivek/Documents/Voice%20Bot/backend/app/services/sms.py#6-19) function, which processes the text message to the user!
